002 -> mol_008 (Fischer-Tropsch-type synthesis of formaldehyde from CO) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_005: mol_006, mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_011, mol_005 (Reductive carboxylation of formate to glyoxylate on greigite) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_006: mol_008, mol_004, mol_003 -> mol_009, mol_005 (Strecker synthesis of aminoacetonitrile from formaldehyde) [Surface]\n  - rxn_007: mol_009, mol_005 -> mol_014, mol_003 (Hydrolysis of aminoacetonitrile to glycine) [Surface]\n  - rxn_008: mol_008 -> mol_010 (Aldol condensation of formaldehyde to glycolaldehyde (formose step 1)) [Surface]\n  - rxn_009: mol_010 -> mol_011 (UV photooxidation of glycolaldehyde to glyoxylic acid) [Surface]\n  - rxn_010: mol_011, mol_003 -> mol_014, mol_005 (Reductive amination of glyoxylic acid to glycine) [Surface]\n  - rxn_011: mol_008, mol_004 -> mol_012 (Cyanohydrin formation: formaldehyde + HCN to glycolonitrile) [Surface]\n  - rxn_012: mol_012, mol_003 -> mol_009, mol_005 (Ammonolysis of glycolonitrile to aminoacetonitrile) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_013: mol_004, mol_005 -> mol_013 (UV-driven hydration of HCN to formamide) [Surface]\n  - rxn_014: mol_013, mol_005 -> mol_006, mol_003 (Hydrolysis of formamide to formate and ammonia) [Surface]\n  - rxn_015: mol_006 -> mol_008 (UV photoreduction of formate to formaldehyde on TiO\u2082) [Surface]\n\nPATHWAYS (10):\n  - P1: Hydrothermal CO\u2082 \u2192 formate \u2192 formaldehyde \u2192 Strecker \u2192 glycine (4 steps)\n  - P2: Hydrothermal CO\u2082 \u2192 CO (RWGS) \u2192 formaldehyde (FTT) \u2192 Strecker \u2192 glycine (4 steps)\n  - P3: Hydrothermal formate \u2192 formaldehyde \u2192 glycolonitrile \u2192 aminoacetonitrile \u2192 glycine (5 steps)\n  - P4: Hydrothermal CO \u2192 FTT formaldehyde \u2192 glycolonitrile \u2192 aminoacetonitrile \u2192 glycine (5 steps)\n  - P5: Hydrothermal formate \u2192 formaldehyde \u2192 formose glycolaldehyde \u2192 glyoxylic acid \u2192 reductive amination \u2192 glycine (5 steps)\n  - P6: Hydrothermal CO \u2192 FTT f