acement of OH by NH\u2083 on a primary carbon is not well-supported; (2) rxn_010 (reductive amination of glyoxylic acid) lacks an explicit reducing agent; (3) Three pathways (P3, P4, P10) contain a Biochemical\u2192Surface backward environmental transition, violating the stated design constraint; (4) rxn_005 (reductive carboxylation) is speculative without strong experimental backing; (5) rxn_008 (formose aldol) lacks a mineral catalyst specification for the Surface environment. Despite these issues, three pathways (P1, P2, P8) are approved with confidence \u2265 0.80, and the overall network architecture is sound. The Strecker synthesis routes (P1, P2) represent the most experimentally validated prebiotic glycine pathways.\",\n  \"approved\": true,\n  \"hub_quality\": 0.90,\n  \"convergence_quality\": 0.87\n}", "parsed_response": {"pathway_evaluations": [{"pathway_id": "P1", "reaction_scores": {"rxn_001": 0.92, "rxn_003": 0.65, "rxn_006": 0.95, "rxn_007": 0.88}, "chemical_feasibility": 0.83, "pathway_coherence": 0.9, "environmental_progression": 0.92, "target_achievement": 0.9, "overall_confidence": 0.86, "feedback": "Classic Strecker route via formate is well-supported. The weakest step is rxn_003 (formate to formaldehyde on native iron) which is thermodynamically uphill and experimentally less robust than the other steps. Mineral catalysts are specified throughout. Environmental flow H\u2192H\u2192S\u2192S is clean.", "approved": true, "problematic_reactions": ["rxn_003"], "suggestions": ["Consider specifying higher temperature/pressure conditions for rxn_003 to improve thermodynamic feasibility", "Add explicit mention of siderite or awaruite as alternative catalysts for formate reduction"]}, {"pathway_id": "P2", "reaction_scores": {"rxn_002": 0.88, "rxn_004": 0.7, "rxn_006": 0.95, "rxn_007": 0.88}, "chemical_feasibility": 0.83, "pathway_coherence": 0.87, "environmental_progression": 0.92, "target_achievement": 0.9, "overall_confidence": 0.85, "feedback": "RWGS t